modules.description: This module provides functions to query, insert, replace, and merge values within JSON structures represented using the `Json_repr_browser.Repr.value` type. It supports navigating and modifying deeply nested JSON values using paths, enabling precise access and updates. Concrete use cases include extracting specific fields from JSON documents, updating nested objects, and combining JSON values with structural merging.

This module provides functions to convert between a browser-specific JSON representation and a common abstract view format. It works with JSON values represented as `value` and abstract views of those values. Use this module to serialize and deserialize JSON data while maintaining compatibility with browser-native structures.

This module provides functions to encode and decode OCaml values to and from JSON representations using specified encodings. It works with JSON values represented as `Json_repr_browser.Repr.value` and OCaml types parameterized over `'t`. Concrete use cases include converting structured OCaml data to JSON for serialization, and parsing JSON input into typed OCaml values according to a defined schema.

This module enables working with JSON data using native browser APIs, supporting both parsing and stringification of JSON values with OCaml and JavaScript string types. It provides direct access to operations for encoding, decoding, querying, and transforming JSON structures, with support for nested navigation and structural merging. Submodules handle representation conversion, schema-based serialization of OCaml values, and manipulation of deeply nested JSON using path-based access. Examples include processing API responses, serializing client-side state, and transforming structured JSON data according to typed schemas.
